Red Stream Update: Concentrations are falling in the Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota districts
The latest report by the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission points to the overall decline in red tide concentrations in the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, spots of blooming water are now reported from the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier districts – indicating decreasing concentrations.
The blooming red tide has a range of about 130 miles of coast from the northern Pinellas District to the southern Lee District.
The spots were observed about 10 miles off the coast in Hillsborough district, but last week it was relatively fewer places.
The red tide was also observed in Pasco district.
